    <string name="info_text">
        "&lt;h3>What?&lt;/h3>\n"
        "&lt;p>This app automatically plays silent background sound when connected to certain Bluetooth devices.&lt;/p>\n"
        "&lt;h3>Why?&lt;/h3>\n"
        "&lt;p>This solves the problem where some Bluetooth speakers miss the first part of the next sound played after silence. This issue is particularly noticeable with intermittent sounds like speech. For example, when listening to audiobooks, the first part of each sentence is often missed.&lt;/p>\n"
        "&lt;h3>How?&lt;/h3>\n"
        "&lt;p>Playing continuously silent (almost inaudible) sound in these speakers prevents completely silent periods and solves this problem.&lt;/p>\n"
        "&lt;h3>When?&lt;/h3>\n"
        "&lt;p>The sound will automatically play when connected to selected Bluetooth devices in settings. Alternatively, you can temporarily play or pause the sound in the top toolbar.&lt;/p>\n"
        "&lt;p>The current auto-play device list is:&lt;/p>\n"
        "&lt;p>&lt;i>%1$s &lt;/i>&lt;/p>"
    </string>

